📊 Poverty Level Analysis in Central Java 2021
Project Description:
This project analyzes poverty levels across regencies and cities in Central Java in 2021 using official data from Statistics Indonesia (BPS).
The analysis focuses on identifying regions with the highest and lowest poverty rates, comparing poverty conditions across areas, and understanding regional socioeconomic disparities. The results are presented through rankings, statistical summaries, and visualizations to provide meaningful insights into poverty distribution throughout Central Java.

Project Objectives:
Analyze poverty levels across regencies and cities in Central Java in 2021.
Compare poverty rates among different regions.
Identify regions with the highest and lowest poverty levels.
Present findings through charts and visualizations.
Strengthen data analysis and interpretation skills using Microsoft Excel.

